The White House Office of Public Engagement recently hosted a listening session with over 70 Black venture capital and private equity stakeholders. The session, titled "Bolstering the U.S. Economy by Closing the Racial Wealth Gap," aimed to discuss ways to promote economic growth in the Black community. Under Secretary Don Cravins from the Minority Business Development Agency moderated the discussion, and Biden-Harris Administration officials shared information about programs available to support Black-owned businesses. The stakeholders emphasized the importance of cultivating a Black investor class and utilizing venture capital and private equity to promote Black wealth creation. The Biden-Harris Administration has been working towards equitable outcomes and opportunities for Black Americans through legislation, programs, and funding. The stakeholders praised the administration's commitment to racial equity and its impact on economic growth and mobility.